added.title: Big Trouble Little Babies
added.description: When they realize they're too small for the rides at an amusement park, the Bears use a magic potion to get bigger.

added.title: Triple T Tigers
added.description: The Bears meet three cool tiger brothers. Grizz wants to be just like the oldest Tiger, TK, but he may not be the best role model.

added.title: Panda's Family
added.description: While exploring a lantern festival, the Bears encounter Panda's long-lost family.

added.title: A Tale of Two Ice Bears
added.description: The Bears accidentally clone Ice Bear and Ice Bear has a hard time adjusting.

added.title: Unica
added.description: The Bears join forces with Unica, the ultimate forest protector.

added.title: For a Few Duncans More
added.description: While trying to photocopy his butt on Chef's fancy new copier Duncan accidentally makes an entire other Duncan. Great! This other Duncan can do all the school stuff while the real Duncan chills. But things go badly when the other Duncan decides to copy himself so he can chill too.

added.title: He Who Wears the Clown
added.description: After trying on the nose of a clown Owen learns that this is how clowns are made and he is stuck as a clown until he can trick someone else into asking to try on the nose.

added.title: Us 'R' Toys
added.description: When Chef brings in some old toys from his childhood he, Duncan and Gwen, each get magically sucked into one of the toys and need to find a way to get back into their own bodies.

added.title: Dream Worriers
added.description: Izzy forgets the ending to her most amazing dream of all time, so the kids travel into her mind to find out what happened.

added.title: Grody to the Maximum
added.description: Cody gets a super cool, new t-shirt. It's SO cool that the kids don't even recognize him, so Cody jumps on the chance to leave his old life behind and become popular.

added.title: Halloween
added.description: In a strange town the gang tries to convince Fred he's mistaken in his firm belief that you can't solve a mystery on Halloween. When an evil witch appears and frightens the town into calling off Halloween, the gang learns this isn't Fred's first run-in with this witch and the true story behind Fred's feelings about Halloween.

added.title: The Curse of Kaniaku
added.description: On a trip to Japan to visit Velma's friend, the gang comes face to face with the ancient crab monster Kaniaku. They attempt to solve a 700 year-old mystery; meanwhile Daphne accidentally becomes a viral media sensation in Japan.

added.title: Vote Velma
added.description: When the ghost of a small town's founder returns to scare off mayoral candidates, the gang decides to run Velma as mayor to bait the ghost. They quickly discover however, that Velma lacks the skill set to make her a popular politician.

added.title: Scroogey Doo
added.description: The Scooby Gang enter Dickens' classic "A Christmas Carol" as they try to get to the bottom of the mysterious ghost tormenting Scrooge in 1843 England. Unfortunately, the Ghosts of Christmas Past, Present and Yet To Come begin to convince Velma she's on a disastrous path of her own.

added.title: In Space
added.description: A very bad parking choice on Fred's part leads the gang to an asteroid mining base in outer space where an alien virus appears to be infecting the crew one by one, turning them into evil skull-headed aliens. The paranoid, terrified gang must try to solve the mystery before the virus reaches them.

added.title: Doo Not Disturb
added.description: To escape a snowstorm, the gang checks into a creepy, massive hotel run by a man very strict about the hotel rules established by his deceased mother. The gang soon discovers the penalty for breaking the hotel rules is a horrifying scolding from the ghost of the owner's mother.

added.title: Silver Scream
added.description: The gang tours an old Hollywood Studio but they soon uncover a mystery concerning the ghost of a silent film comedy star who has returned to make sure his recently discovered final film is never seen.

added.title: Fright of Hand
added.description: Fred lives out his childhood dream of being a stage magician as he and the gang go undercover at a private magic club being terrorized by a mutant Rabbit monster.

added.title: Greece Is the Word
added.description: We travel back to Ancient Greece, where the gang plays unique roles in a Greek Mystery involving the mythological spider woman, Arachne, and her attempts to disrupt the royal wedding that would unite two great cities.

added.title: American Goth
added.description: Shaggy is surprised to see his old childhood first crush has become a Goth. Embarrassed that he hasn't changed at all, Shaggy attends a Goth party with the gang, allowing himself to become initiated into the Goth culture, much to Scooby's concern - especially when the gang discovers there's a ferocious plant monster roaming the corridors of the abandoned hospital the Goth's call home.

added.title: Ollie Ollie In-Come Free!
added.description: When our mystery solving gang agrees to help Ricky Gervais with a haunted antique Egyptian statue of a cat, they find themselves embroiled in a confrontation with the ancient goddess Bast in mummy form!

added.title: The Cursed Cabinet of Professor Madds Markson!
added.description: When our mystery solving gang accepts the invitation to spend one night in the haunted Savannah Hotel in Las Vegas before its controlled demolition, they find that they're not alone. Famous magicians and entertainers Penn and Teller have also accepted the challenge. The winner gets a million bucks. While the loser may not make it out alive because the place is cursed and haunted by the ghost of infamous illusionist Professor Madds Markson and his horrible monster!

added.title: Attack of the Weird Al-Osaurus!
added.description: Driving through the Rocky Mountains, the Mystery Inc. gang discovers a sleep-away accordion camp run by none other than Weird Al Yankovic! But there is no accordion joy when a horrible dinosaur attacks the camp. Can our heroes and Weird Al solve this prehistoric mystery or are they destined to become dino-food?

added.title: When Urkel-Bots Go Bad!
added.description: When Steve Urkel enlists the help of our mystery solving gang to track down the rampaging Urkel-Bot, they stumble onto a deeper mystery. It seems the Urkel-Bot has gone haywire and escaped a Chicago Museum! The mystery deepens with the appearance of a Technomancer, controlling all the robots! Can our gang and Urkel survive an onslaught of the Technomancer's angry robots? And, more importantly, can our gang survive Urkel?

added.title: The Fastest Fast Food Fiend!
added.description: When Scooby and Shaggy compete in a fast food eating competition sponsored by the Doc Tally restaurant chain, they meet their ultimate challenge eating against none other than comedian Jim Gaffigan! And there's a horrible monster trying to stop the whole contest from finishing. Can Shaggy, Scooby and our mystery solving gang team up with Jim Gaffigan to save the fast food competition, and themselves?

added.title: Space Station Scooby!
added.description: When Neil deGrasse Tyson gets trapped on the International Space Station with a horrible monster, Bill Nye arrives to save his good friend with the help of Velma and our mystery solving gang. Arriving at the space station in the nick of time, our heroes work with these two scientific minds to separate the science from the science fiction when a Tardigrade monster wreaks havoc on the ship.

added.title: Now You Sia, Now You Don't!
added.description: When Daphne gets a call from her good friend singer-songwriter Sia, the gang finds themselves in a mystery involving an evil demon ghost that has taken the shape of Sia as a ghostly doppelganger. And this ghost is getting Sia in hot water by stealing countless gems and jewelry. Can our gang prove her innocence? Can they catch the true thief? Or will the ghostly doppelganger catch them instead?

added.title: The Nightmare Ghost of Psychic U!
added.description: When the Mystery Inc. gang gets lost in the Pocono Mountains of Pennsylvania, they stumble into Psychic University. They meet Whoopi Goldberg, who's been going to psychic school for a number of months now. She's so close to graduating when a nightmare ghost attacks the school and seems to want to destroy all the students. Can our heroes see their future? Or is it all blank because they don't have one?

added.title: Quit Clowning!
added.description: Shaggy and Scooby take the gang to meet their good friend actor and comedian, Kenan Thompson. He's preparing to broadcast a special one-man show to save a struggling old TV station in Atlanta, Georgia. But when a Ghost Clown attacks, they all freak. It seems that all the many characters Kenan has created for his special one-man show will never see the light of day if the ghost clown has his way.

added.title: The Sword, the Fox, and the Scooby Doo!
added.description: When our mystery solving gang is driving in Japan, they are stopped by none-other than famous actor Mark Hamill. He's in town for a high school reunion, but a terrible Fox Monster has attacked the reunion and kidnapped one of Mark's favorite old teachers. From reliving high school rivalries to surviving haunted, abandoned temples, Mark Hamill and our gang must face a ghastly Fox Monster in order to not only save the day, but their own lives.

added.title: What the Hex Is Going On?
added.description: When the gang visits the Weatherby estate, they must investigate a mysterious voice and a ghost who demands the family return its fortune to a neighboring clan.

added.title: Never Ape an Ape Man
added.description: The gang is hired by Daphne's uncle, a famous director, as extras in his latest project. But the star of the show is a real nasty ape.

added.title: Foul Play in Funland
added.description: The gang investigates a haunted seaside amusement park.

added.title: The Backstage Rage
added.description: A sinister puppet master manipulates the gang's investigation of a case of counterfeit.

added.title: Bedlam in the Big Top
added.description: A ghost clown haunts a small circus, using hypnotism to bend locals to his will.

added.title: A Gaggle of Galloping Ghosts
added.description: The gang visits Franken Castle, which seems to be crowded with famous inhabitants Dracula, the Monster and Wolf Man.

added.title: Scooby-Doo and a Mummy, Too
added.description: The gang helps a professor set up an ancient Egypt exhibit but the star of the display keeps vanishing.

added.title: Which Witch Is Which?
added.description: A zombie walks in front of the Mystery Machine as the gang heads into the bayou for a fishing trip, leading to a real witch hunt.

added.title: Go Away Ghost Ship
added.description: The gang sets out to solve the mystery of a ghostly pirate seemingly bent on avenging his capture by a shipping magnate's ancestor.

added.title: Spooky Space Kook
added.description: The gang stumbles across a UFO's landing site when the Mystery Machine runs out of gas on a deserted road.

added.title: Scarebear
added.description: The mayor of Crystal Cove has his camping trip ruined by the evil Scarebear and the gang is on the case.

added.title: Wrath of the Krampus
added.description: When the strange appearance of a mean goat-man demon named Krampus terrorizes naughty kids all over town, the Mystery Inc. gang decide to look into things. Chasing Krampus all over Crystal Cove, they try to second-guess the crazy, evil goat-man's motives and who could be behind the mystery.

added.title: Heart of Evil
added.description: Dr. Zin, of Jonny Quest fame, wreaks havoc on Crystal Cove.

added.title: Theater of Doom
added.description: Life imitates art in Crystal Cove's annual Haunted Historical Pageant.

added.title: Aliens Among Us
added.description: The gang investigates some potential extra-terrestrial life in Crystal Cove with the help of Velma's mother.

added.title: In Dreams
added.description: Steven's dreams start broadcasting onto his bedroom TV.

added.title: Bismuth Casual
added.description: Pearl invites Bismuth to the roller rink for a lesson on how to forge human relationships.

added.title: Together Forever
added.description: Connie has a really clear vision for her future. Steven wants to make sure he'll be a part of it.

added.title: Growing Pains
added.description: Steven visits a doctor for the first time.

added.title: Mr. Universe
added.description: Greg takes Steven on the road to find the origins of the Universe name.

added.title: Fragments
added.description: Steven heads to the woods to train with a powerful mentor.

added.title: Homeworld Bound
added.description: Steven heads to the Diamonds for advice on how to control his new powers.

added.title: Everything's Fine
added.description: Steven insists that everything is fine.

added.title: I Am My Monster
added.description: Everything is not fine.

added.title: The Future
added.description: Steven is finally ready to move on.

added.title: The Filth
added.description: Ben is tasked with cleaning the Rust Bucket. But when he is tricked into letting the villainous and vile Fly Guys steal it, he must chase them down before they create an unstoppable maggot monster with sights firmly set on destroying Las Vegas.

added.title: Waterfilter
added.description: Ben, Gwen, and Max's trip to Niagara Falls is cut short by the horrid Hydromanders, creatures menacing them and their fellow tourists.

added.title: The Ring Leader
added.description: While winning big on a Sumo Slammers video game, Ben gets the idea to win a wrestling match for real until an intimidating wrestler named Iron Kyle decides to make it a true challenge.

added.title: Riding the Storm Out
added.description: Ben and Gwen's camping trip is interrupted by the emotionless Weatherheads (Gust-o, Hail-o, & Shock-o) but a malfunctioning Omnitrix firing out a mishmash of aliens may not be the forecast for success.

added.title: The Clocktopus
added.description: In a peaceful coastal town, Ben must not only face the archaic antagonist Steam Smythe and his latest creation, the Clocktopus, but also his deepest, darkest fear: Squids!

added.title: Take 10
added.description: While trying to film his own indie film, Ben accidentally allows the Bug Gang to go free and when he takes the fight to their hidden lair Ben has to take on their narcissistic leader, the Ant Queen.

added.title: Growing Pains
added.description: During a stop at the superstore Shoppe, Ben and Gwen are transformed into babies by nanny-gone-nuts Nanny Nightmare, who will stop at nothing to reshape the world in the image of her daycare.

added.title: Shhh!
added.description: While chilling at a monastery with a no-noise policy, Ben can't keep quiet and accidentally awakens a dangerous Dragon hidden in a secret chamber below the hallowed halls. A job that might be too much for even Diamondhead to handle.

added.title: Brief Career of Lucky Girl
added.description: When a wizard cos player gets his hands on a real, magical wand at Comic Con, Ben enlists Gwen to help stop Hex from retrieving it by tricking the wicked warlock into thinking she is a powerful magic-wielder in her own right: the one and only Lucky Girl!

added.title: Animo Farm
added.description: Ben stumbles into Dr. Animo's secret lab now ruled by his superior mutants, the Alphas, and must help the lesser animals escape while stuck as Stinkfly.

added.title: And Then There Were 10
added.description: Ben discovers the Omnitrix, and when it attaches itself to Ben's wrist, he discovers it allows him to become any one of ten alien heroes.

added.title: The More Things Change Part 1
added.description: Now on his own, Ben sets out to be a solo superhero, with new alien heroes at his disposal, but Grandpa Max has other plans. (Introducing Rook, Malware, Khyber, Nemetrix alien Crabdozer, new Ben aliens Feedback & Blox, Pakmar.)

added.title: Washington B.C.
added.description: Ben must use the Omnitrix to transform into alien heroes to battle Dr. Amino and his transmorphed dinosaurs running rampant in Washington DC.

added.title: The More Things Change Part 2
added.description: Ben and Rook discover an underground city beneath Bellwood populated with aliens! But who is terrorizing them? (Introducing Nemetrix alien BugLizard, & Ben alien Shocksquatch, Psyphon, Fistina, Bubblehelmet, Liam.)

added.title: The Krakken
added.description: While stopped at a lakefront campsite, Ben has a chance encounter with a Loch Ness type sea monster called a Krakken, controlled by an evil poacher.

added.title: A Jolt from the Past
added.description: Alien pests from Ben's youth come back, but now they need Ben's help. (Introducing Fistrick, & new Ben alien Gravattack.)

added.title: Trouble Helix
added.description: Flashback episode: Young Ben, Gwen, and Grandpa Max visit Azmuth on Galvan Prime. There, they have their first encounter with Malware, a corrupted Mechamorph who's determined to make Azmuth cure him, by any means!

added.title: Permanent Retirement
added.description: Grandpa, Gwen and Ben visit an old maid relative only to find that her retirement community has been overtaken by a shapeshifting aliens called Limax.

added.title: Hunted
added.description: Three alien bounty hunters are hot on Ben's trail. But one of them is a secret agent trying to make sure the Omnitrix does not fall into evil hands.

added.title: Have I Got a Deal for You
added.description: Ben and Rook must stop a giant rampaging alien from destroying Bellwood while dealing with a peace-loving alien-rights activist who doesn't want it hurt. (Introducing Hokestar, Solid Plugg 1st appearance, Pax, Sunder.)

added.title: Tourist Trap
added.description: While messing with the World's Largest Rubberband Ball at a tourist trap, Ben accidently releases some mischievous electrical creatures.

added.title: It Was Them
added.description: Dr. Animo has escaped his Plumber prison, and Ben and Rook must track him down before he turns the world into his personal mutant ant farm! (Introducing Nemetrix alien Slamworm, Galvan Plumbers Blukic and Driba, Arctiguana, new Ben alien Crashhopper.)

added.title: So Long, and Thanks for All the Smoothies
added.description: When Ben and Rook investigate a mysterious alien ghost ship, they discover that Argit and the Vreedle Brothers are fighting for possession of a doomsday device! (Introducing Solid Plugg.)

added.title: Kevin 11
added.description: After a big argument with Max, Ben rebels by going out on his own in the Big Apple and makes friends with Kevin 11, who has plans for the Omnitrix.

added.title: Hot Stretch
added.description: Ben and Rook encounter a race of elastic, hot-blooded aliens in Undertown who want to use a stolen nuclear fusion engine to activate a volcano! (Introducing Ester, Seebik & the Kraaho.)

added.title: The Alliance
added.description: As Fourarms, Ben works to thwart an armored truck robbery by a tough female gang leader named Joey, who delivers a disturbing message from Vilgax.

added.title: Of Predators and Prey Part 1
added.description: After a heated argument, Ben and Rook go their separate ways, giving Khyber the Huntsman his best chance to capture Ben! (Introducing Dr. Psychobos, new Nemetrix aliens Mucillator & Terroranchula; new Ben alien Ballweevil.)

added.title: Last Laugh
added.description: Ben's fear of clowns emerges at an unfortunate time when our heroes stumble upon a wicked circus with a psychic vampire clown named Zomobozo.

added.title: Of Predators and Prey Part 2
added.description: While trapped in Khyber's ship, Ben learns details about the origin of the Nemetrix, and the link between Khyber, Malware, and Dr. Psychobos! (Introducing new Nemetrix alien Tyrannopede.)

added.title: Lucky Girl
added.description: Ben battles an evil sorcerer whose power whose emanates from mystic charms, one of which turns Gwen into her own superhero named Lucky Girl.

added.title: Plastic Man Saves the World
added.description: Plastic Man feels shuffled off to the side as the Justice League battles Brainiac so he takes it upon himself to infiltrate the alien's ship on his own and thwart the villain's plans.

added.title: Field Trip
added.description: A group of teenage superheroes are being shown around the Fortress of Solitude when they inadvertently cause the phantom zone projector to trap Superman and release three Kryptonian criminals.

added.title: Rage of the Red Lanterns
added.description: Chased by the Red Lanterns, Lobo seeks sanctuary with the Justice League. As the League attempts to stave off the Red Lanterns, Lobo reveals the real reason he wants shelter in the Watchtower, he wants access to a powerful space weapon being held by our heroes.

added.title: Freezer Burn
added.description: Batman and Firestorm team up to fight their respective cold villains, Mr. Freeze and Killer Frost. Complications arise when Firestorm's infatuation for the wily Ms. Frost gets the best of him.

added.title: Inside Job
added.description: In a "Fantastic Voyage" like adventure, Atom shrinks Batman and Wonder Woman so they can enter Superman's bloodstream and destroy a lethal nanite virus.

added.title: Would You Like to Enter Prime Empire?
added.description: While investigating a heist, the ninja discover Prime Empire, a legendary unreleased arcade game that suddenly takes control of all other games in Ninjago.

added.title: Dyer Island
added.description: When the ninja connect Jay's disappearance to Prime Empire, they set out to Dyer Island to seek answers from the game's designer, the elusive Milton Dyer.

added.title: Level Thirteen
added.description: Cyrus Borg discovers a shocking secret about Prime Empire, while the ninja battle an escaped Mechanic in their attempt to reach Level Thirteen and enter the game themselves.

added.title: Superstar Rockin' Jay
added.description: Now inside the Prime Empire game, the ninja find themselves in unfamiliar territory, ignorant of the rules of this world, as they try to find Zane and escape Unagami's army of Red Visors.

added.title: I Am Okino
added.description: Inside one of the game zones, a Samurai named Okino faces a crisis of faith when he repeatedly fails to lead a series of Masters to victory, causing him to lose all hope, until some familiar ninja arrive.

added.title: Everett's Trap/Kazami vs. Mc Q
added.description: Shun and Masato head to Tokyo's Battle Island to discuss plans for hosting public Bakugan battles. Upon landing, they quickly learn it's a set up! The two are now stranded and faced with heaps of brawlers, who are all looking to bring them down!/ Shun and Masato manage to fend off a horde of brawlers on Battle Island, but they quickly learn that was only a diversion- one of Kazami's research centers is under siege. The two must find a way off the island and head off to defend the research center.

added.title: The Awesome Burger Brawl/Master and Apprentice
added.description: The Burger Joint is hosting a hamburger eating contest to promote their new Bakugan themed burger! The contest gets underway without a hitch, that is until Sophie and the Bakugan Preservation Society crash the event with a bakugan brawl!/ A wealthy man, Mr. Gold, has duped Storm and Ajit, and trapped them in his personal prison. But no prison can hold the cunning phantom thief Storm and his former apprentice, Ajit for long.

added.title: Bakugan Uproar/The Fusion Bakugan Sabrus
added.description: While the Awesome Brawlers' Bakugan squabble about what to watch on TV at Studio D, Haavik unleashes his newly created five-faction fusion Bakugan: Sabrus on the city of Los Volmos./ The Awesome Brawlers are in pursuit of Haavik and his new Bakugan, Sabrus but all they can find is the trail of destruction that Sabrus has left behind. They need to figure out where Haavik and his Bakugan will strike next and put an end to his rampage.

added.title: Ancient Golden Bakugan Garillion/The Name of Infinity
added.description: The ancient golden Bakugan, Garillion Infinity has come to Los Volmos to try to put an end to Haavik's show of destruction and chaos but upon arriving he turns his sights on Drago, Dan and the Awesome Brawlers./ Haavik and his five-faction fusion Bakugan Sabrus take their rampage to AAAnimus' headquarters. The Awesome Brawlers quickly track down the rampaging duo and face off!

added.title: In the Darkness/Indecisive Emily
added.description: An encounter with Storm and his trick rose leaves Magnus temporarily blinded and unable to brawl. With the help of an unlikely partner, Magnus pursues Storm in an attempt to defeat him and restore his vision./ Emily obtains a second Bakugan named Chrissy. It's soon obvious that Emily is having trouble brawling with both Chrissy and Webam, and it's up to Dan, Drago and Gillator to teach them how to brawl as a team.

added.title: Te Gustaria Entrar a Primer Imperio?
added.description: Mientras investigan un robo, los ninjas descubren Primer Imperio, un videojuego que  toma el control de todos los demás videojuegos de Ninjago.

added.title: Isla Dyer
added.description: Cuando los ninjas relacionan la desaparición de Jay con Primer Imperio, van a la Isla Dyer para buscar respuestas del diseñador del juego, Milton Dyer.

added.title: Nivel Trece
added.description: Cyrus Borg descubre un secreto sobre Primer Imperio y  los ninjas enfrentan al Mecánico que escapó e intenta alcanzar el Nivel 13 para entrar al juego.

added.title: Jay Estrella del Rock
added.description: Dentro de Primer Imperio, los ninjas se encuentran en un territorio desconocido e intentan encontrar a Jay y escapar de los Visores Rojos de Unagami.

added.title: Yo Soy Okino
added.description: Dentro de una de las zonas de juego, un Samurai llamado Okino se enfrenta a una crisis de fe cuando no logra que los Maestros obtengan la victoria.

added.title: Por unos Duncans mas
added.description: Mientras trataba de fotocopiar su trasero en la nueva y elegante fotocopiadora del Chef, Duncan accidentalmente hace otro Duncan completo. iExcelente! Este otro Duncan puede hacer todas las cosas de la escuela mientras el verdadero Duncan se enfría. Pero las cosas van mal cuando el otro Duncan decide copiarse a sí mismo para poder relajarse también.

added.title: Quiero Ser Payaso
added.description: Después de probarse la nariz de un payaso, Owen se entera de que así es como se hacen los payasos y está atrapado como un payaso hasta que puede engañar a otra persona para que le pida probarse la nariz.

added.title: Somos Juguetes
added.description: Cuando el Chef trae algunos juguetes viejos de su infancia, él, Duncan y Gwen, cada uno es absorbido mágicamente por uno de los juguetes y necesitan encontrar una manera de volver a sus propios cuerpos.

added.title: Suenos Problematicos
added.description: Izzy olvida el final de su sueño más asombroso de todos los tiempos, por lo que los niños viajan a su mente para descubrir qué sucedió.

added.title: Grody al Maximo
added.description: Cody recibe una camiseta nueva y genial. Es TAN genial que los niños ni siquiera lo reconocen, así que Cody aprovecha la oportunidad de dejar atrás su antigua vida y volverse popular.

added.title: La Suciedad
added.description: A Ben le encargan la tarea de limpiar la Chatarra, pero cuando, engañado por los viles villanos Fly Guys, permite que se lo roben, debe perseguirlos antes de que fabriquen una larva monstruosa imparable con un objetivo claro: destruir Las Vegas.

added.title: Filtro Acuatico
added.description: El viaje de Ben, Gwen y Max a las Cataratas del Niágara se ve interrumpido por los horribles Hydromanders: unas criaturas que los amenazan a ellos y a los demás turistas.

added.title: El Lider Del Ring
added.description: Cuando Ben tiene una racha ganadora en un videojuego, se le ocurre una idea para ganar un partido real de lucha, hasta que un luchador intimidante decide convertirlo en un verdadero desafío.

added.title: Sobreviviendo A La Tormenta
added.description: El campamento de Ben y Gwen se ve interrumpido por los gélidos Weatherheads -Gust-o, Hail-o, & Shock-o-, pero un Omnitrix que funciona mal y dispara un montón de extraterrestres podría no ser un pronóstico de éxito.

added.title: El Relopulpo
added.description: En una pacífica ciudad costera, Ben no solo debe enfrentarse a Vapor Smythe -su arcaico antagonista- y a su última creación, el Relopulpo... isino que también debe enfrentarse a su temor más profundo y oscuro: los calamares!

added.title: Toma 10
added.description: Mientras Ben intenta rodar su propia película independiente, por accidente libera a una pandilla de insectos y, cuando la lucha se traslada a su guarida oculta, Ben debe enfrentarse a su líder narcisista: La Hormiga Reina.

added.title: Cambio De Edad
added.description: Durante una parada en la megatienda Shoppë, Nanny Nightmare -una niñera que se volvió loca- transforma a Ben y Gwen en bebés. Y nada la detendrá en su intento de reorganizar el mundo a imagen y semejanza de su guardería.

added.title: Shhh
added.description: Mientras Ben se relaja en un monasterio con una política de silencio, no puede quedarse callado y, por accidente, despierta a un peligroso Dragón oculto en una recámara secreta bajo los salones sagrados...una tarea que podría ser demasiado para manejar, iincluso para Diamante!

added.title: La Breve Carrera De La Nina Suertuda
added.description: Cuando un hechicero jugador de cosplay pone las manos sobre una varita mágica real en la convención Comic Con, Ben consigue la ayuda de Gwen para impedir que Hex la recupere: Gwen engaña al hechicero malvado y le hace creer que es una poderosa maga...ila única e inimitable Niña Suertuda!

added.title: Rebelion En La Granja
added.description: Ben encuentra el laboratorio secreto del Doctor Ánimo -ahora gobernado por los alfas, sus mutantes superiores- y debe ayudar a los animales inferiores mientras está atrapado en forma de Insectoide.

added.title: En Suenos
added.description: Los sueños de Steven comienzan a transmitirse en el televisor de su dormitorio.

added.title: Bismuto Casual
added.description: Perla invita a Bismuto a la pista de patinaje para darle una lección sobre cómo forjar relaciones humanas.

added.title: Juntos por Siempre
added.description: Connie tiene una visión muy clara de su futuro, y Steven quiere asegurarse de ser parte de esa visión.

added.title: Duele Crecer
added.description: Steven va al médico por primera vez.

added.title: Sr. Universo
added.description: Greg lleva a Steven de viaje para encontrar los orígenes del nombre del Universo.

added.title: Fragmentos
added.description: Steven se dirige al bosque para entrenarse con un poderoso mentor.

added.title: Rumbo al Planeta Madre
added.description: Steven acude a las Diamantes para pedirles consejos sobre cómo controlar sus nuevos poderes.

added.title: Todo Esta Bien
added.description: Steven insiste en que todo está bien.

added.title: Soy Mi Monstruo
added.description: No todo está bien.

added.title: El Futuro
added.description: Steven por fin está listo para avanzar.

added.title: Festival of Hearts
added.description: When two greedy gnomes steal Love-a-Lot's gift-making crystal heart, the Care Bears must get it back in time for the Festival of Hearts that they are holding for the Whiffles. In doing so, they have to teach the gnomes the meaning of caring.

added.title: An Almost Eggless Easter
added.description: When the Easter Bunny's beautifully-painted eggs are drained of their color, it looks like Dibble will miss her first Easter egg hunt - she's really been looking forward to it. The Bears must find a way to repaint all the eggs before the big day.

added.title: A Wish-Full Reunion
added.description: Mysterious flying hearts appear in Care-A-Lot and bring Wish Bear to the Silver Lining. She joins the Care Bears on a mission to bring a mystical mother bird's missing baby chicks home, and give a new home to an orphan bird.

added.title: The Birthday That Wasn't
added.description: Dibble misunderstands the Bears' intentions when they secretly make a plush toy Whiffle for her "Un-birthday." Thinking it's real and that the Bears love it more than they love her, she steals it and plans to leave it in the forest. She has second thoughts and returns her "rival" to her friends, only to learn that it's a gift to show their love for her.

added.title: The Big Rumble
added.description: A family of comically raucous rocks moves in near a Whiffle garden and drives them to distraction with their ground-pounding games. Funshine gets the rocks to leave. But when he learns their ground-pounding creates new soil, he must convince them to come back.

added.title: Win, Lose or Daffy
added.description: A day playing miniature golf is fun for everyone but Baby Daffy, who believes he must beat everyone else at the game. At the end of the day, all but Daffy are having a good time regardless of how they scored.

added.title: Wrong!
added.description: On an orchard outing, picking bushels of fresh apples for Granny's home-baked pies, the Baby Looney Tunes encounter Melissa, who is in a mood to tell everyone that her method of apple picking is the only way.

added.title: Cock-A-Doodle-Doo-It!
added.description: On their first farm visit, the Baby Looney Tunes meet a young, dispirited rooster named Baby Foghorn Leghorn. They work together to build his self-confidence, unleashing powers of persuasion and elocution that even Foghorn never knew he had.

added.title: Backstage Bugs
added.description: Baby Bugs can't wait to see his favorite children's musical group, The Wormies, and he absolutely thrills to the notion of possibly meeting his personal hero, Willie Wormie, backstage after the show. But Bugs fails to heed Floyd's warning about staying with the group in the crowded arena and suffers consequences when he gets separated from Floyd.

added.title: Bend it Like Petunia
added.description: The Baby Looney Tunes learn all about soccer from Floyd, who surprisingly is an enthused soccer expert. At first awkward, Baby Petunia works the hardest and displays the best sportsmanlike attitude, eventually becoming the very finest all-around soccer player of all the Baby Looney Tunes.
